      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 114591927686108806, guid: ee8ad5531e02f4f0eb2d4187ec62c699, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: 'This effect makes use of a particle system using ''mesh render mode''
        and a custom unlit shader. Mesh render mode instances a mesh to each particle
        position. The particle is orientated towards the particle velocity, which
        are moved around in a random manner using the ''noise'' module to make it
        look like the fire flies are flying around.


        The Shader is a two
        pass shader that uses one pass to render the fire fly body and another for
        the flapping wings. The wings use a different UV channel and have a sprite
        sheet texture assigned to them which is animated by the particle system by
        making the ''texture sheet animation'' only affect UV1 (or the 2nd UV channel).'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 114591927686108806, guid: ee8ad5531e02f4f0eb2d4187ec62c699, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_fontStyle
      value: 0
